<h1 id="zmodel-feature-pack">zModel Feature Pack</h1>
<p>zModel feature pack provides features, which extend basic zModel framework:</p>
<ol>
<li><a href="javascript:void(0)" onClick="scrollToAnchor('workflow-activities');">Workflow activities</a> for 3 models: Linear, Logistic and Softmax regression.</li>
<li><a href="javascript:void(0)" onClick="scrollToAnchor('rest-api');">REST API</a>, which allows to:
<ul>
<li>query zModel framework data (models and scores)</li>
<li>run the model on particular input data</li>
</ul></li>
</ol>
<blockquote>
<p>zModel feature pack requires Orchestration plugin and zModel framework to be installed in ServiceNow instance.</p>
</blockquote>
<h2 name="workflow-activities">Workflow activities</h2>
<p>Workflow activities provide the ability to use predictive models in ServiceNow workflows for any business/ITIL application. zModel activities can be found on <em>Packs</em> tab in Workflow editor:</p>
<p align="center">
<img src="11-zmfp.png" style="width:40%;">
</p>
<h4 id="how-to-use-zmodel-workflow-activities">How to use zModel workflow activities</h4>
<ol>
<li>Drag and drop the corresponding model to the workflow</li>
<li>Connect activity (input and output)</li>
<li>Specify model parameters.</li>
</ol>
<p align="center">
<img src="2-zmfp.png" style="width:90%;">
</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Model parameters can be specified manually when creating a workflow or during runtime using scratchpad variables or workflow input parameters.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The following parameters should be specified:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Model</strong> - sys_id of the corresponding model in zModel framework.</li>
<li><strong>Input Data</strong> - input data, which should be scored by the model. This data should be passed to the model in runtime using workflow input variables or scratchpad variables.</li>
<li><strong>Transaction Reference</strong> - optional parameter, which may be used as a unique transaction ID or as a specific score reference. Can be defined during runtime of when designing a workflow.</li>
</ol>
<h4 id="how-to-pass-data-to-the-model-activity">How to pass data to the model activity</h4>
<p>Input data can be passed to the model activity using workflow input variables (most common use case):</p>
<ol>
<li>Define a workflow input variable.</li>
<li>Populate the variable in a script.</li>
<li>Add a reference to the workflow variable in the model parameters. You can reference the variable as<code>${workflow.inputs.u_input_data}</code>, where <code>u_input_data</code> is a name of the workflow input variable.</li>
</ol>
<p align="center">
<img src="3-zmfp.png" style="width:90%;">
</p>
<p>Using scratchpad variable (legacy option):</p>
<ol>
<li>Define a scratchpad variable prior to the model activity, populate that variable with the corresponding data you need to score (this can be done in <em>Run Script</em> activity):</li>
</ol>

<ol start="2">
<li>Use that variable in the model (activity) parameters. You can reference scratchpad variable as <code>${workflow.scratchpad.input_data}</code></li>
</ol>
<h4 id="how-to-read-the-model-output-data">How to read the model output data</h4>
<p align="center">
<img src="701-zmfp.png" style="width:90%;">
</p>
<p>Model output stored as an object in <em>Score</em> activity variable. If you have multiple models in the workflow then multiple <em>Score</em> objects will be available.</p>
<p align="center">
<img src="7-zmfp.png" style="width:30%;">
</p>
<p>You can read the output <em>Score</em> object using the following options:</p>
<ol>
<li>If you need to read model's output and put it as <em>an input parameter</em> in to some other activities then you can reference it as <code>${data.get(x).Score}</code>, where <code>x</code> is a model reference number from <em>Data</em> tab in a workflow editor.</li>
<li>If you want to access model's output in a script then you can use the following reference - <code>data.get(x).Score</code>.</li>
</ol>

<h2 name="rest-api">REST API</h2>
<p>zModel framework REST API based on the out-of-the-box ServiceNow Table API (#1-#7) and a custom scripted web service (#8).</p>
<p>The following requests supported by zModel REST API:</p>
<ol>
<li><a href="javascript:void(0)" onClick="scrollToAnchorH4('1-get-the-list-of-models');">GET the list of Models</a></li>
<li><a href="javascript:void(0)" onClick="scrollToAnchorH4('2-get-the-list-of-scores');">GET the list of Scores</a></li>
<li><a href="javascript:void(0)" onClick="scrollToAnchorH4('3-get-the-specific-model-by-sys_id');">GET the specific model by sys_id</a></li>
<li><a href="javascript:void(0)" onClick="scrollToAnchorH4('4-get-the-list-of-scores-by-model-sys_id');">GET the list of scores by Model sys_id</a></li>
<li><a href="javascript:void(0)" onClick="scrollToAnchorH4('5-get-the-specific-score-by-sys_id');">GET the specific score by sys_id</a></li>
<li><a href="javascript:void(0)" onClick="scrollToAnchorH4('6-create-model');">CREATE model</a></li>
<li><a href="javascript:void(0)" onClick="scrollToAnchorH4('7-update-model');">UPDATE model</a></li>
<li><a href="javascript:void(0)" onClick="scrollToAnchorH4('8-run-score');">RUN score</a></li>
</ol>
<blockquote>
<p>ServiceNow Table API reference: <a href="https://docs.servicenow.com/bundle/geneva-servicenow-platform/page/integrate/inbound_rest/concept/c_TableAPI.html">https://docs.servicenow.com/bundle/geneva-servicenow-platform/page/integrate/inbound_rest/concept/c_TableAPI.html</a></p>
</blockquote>
<h5 id="security">Security</h5>
<p>For all requests <code>x_elsr_z_model.basic_user</code> role (comes with zModel framework application) should be assigned to a user account in order to performs REST calls.</p>
<p>For requests #1-7 <code>rest_service</code> role should be assigned to a user account.</p>
<p>For request #8 <code>rest.score.calculation</code> role should be assigned to the account.</p>
<h5 id="response">Response</h5>
<p>ServiceNow responds with a JSON object, which contains information about the transaction itself and the corresponding record or list of records.</p>

    var data = request.body.data;
	var res = {};
	var zM = new x_elsr_z_model.zModel();
	if (data.modelType=="Linear Regression") {
		res = zM.linearModel(data.inputData,data.modelSys_id,data.externalReference);
	}
	if (data.modelType=="Logistic Regression") {
		res = zM.logisticModel(data.inputData,data.modelSys_id,data.externalReference);
	}
	if (data.modelType=="Softmax Regression") {
		res = zM.softmaxModel(data.inputData,data.modelSys_id,data.externalReference);
	}
	if (res.status==77) {
		response.setStatus(201);
	} else {
		response.setStatus(400);
	}
	response.setBody(res);
})(request, response);]]></operation_script><operation_uri>/api/x_elsr_zmodel_fp/v1/zmodel</operation_uri><produces>application/json,application/xml,text/xml</produces><produces_customized>false</produces_customized><relative_path>/</relative_path><request_example/><requires_acl_authorization>true</requires_acl_authorization><requires_authentication>true</requires_authentication><short_description/><sys_class_name>sys_ws_operation</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>andrew.pishchulin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2017-07-21 17:52:23</sys_created_on><sys_customer_update>true</sys_customer_update><sys_id>2f79d31adb0807c0cc38f7fdbf961923</sys_id><sys_mod_count>6</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Run score</sys_name><sys_package display_value="zModel Feature Pack" source="x_elsr_zmodel_fp">07e3ae96db8407c0cc38f7fdbf961971</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_replace_on_upgrade>false</sys_replace_on_upgrade><sys_scope display_value="zModel Feature Pack">07e3ae96db8407c0cc38f7fdbf961971</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_ws_operation_2f79d31adb0807c0cc38f7fdbf961923</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>andrew.pishchulin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2017-07-21 18:17:00</sys_updated_on><web_service_definition display_value="zModel REST API">fb59531adb0807c0cc38f7fdbf96199a</web_service_definition><web_service_version display_value="v1">c3f9931adb0807c0cc38f7fdbf9619a1</web_service_version></sys_ws_operation></record_update>
